    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\"/>\n  <title>Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) Demo</title>\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\">\n  <style>\n    :root {\n      --bg:#0f1724;\n      --panel:#0b1220;\n      --muted:#9aa6bf;\n      --accent:#7dd3fc;\n      --card:#0b1220;\n      --node:#132033;\n      --highlight:#1f6feb;\n      --success:#16a34a;\n      --danger:#ef4444;\n    }\n    html,body { height:100%; margin:0; font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, \"Helvetica Neue\", Arial; background:linear-gradient(180deg,#051025 0%, #071426 50%, #021018 100%); color:var(--muted); }\n    .wrap { display:flex; gap:16px; padding:18px; box-sizing:border-box; height:100vh; }\n    .col { background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.02), rgba(255,255,255,0.01)); border-radius:10px; padding:12px; box-sizing:border-box; flex:1; min-width:280px; display:flex; flex-direction:column; }\n    .col.small { flex:0 0 360px; }\n    h1 { margin:6px 0 12px 0; font-size:18px; color:var(--accent); }\n    textarea { width:100%; height:260px; resize:vertical; font-family: monospace; font-size:13px; color:#e6eef8; background:transparent; border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04); padding:10px; border-radius:6px; outline:none; }\n    .controls { display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:10px; }\n    button { background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.02), rgba(255,255,255,0.01)); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); color:var(--muted); padding:8px 10px; border-radius:6px; cursor:pointer; font-size:13px; }\n    button.primary { background:linear-gradient(180deg,#0369a1,#0ea5e9); border:0; color:white; box-shadow:0 6px 20px rgba(3,105,161,0.12); }\n    button.danger { background:linear-gradient(180deg,#b91c1c,#ef4444); color:white; border:0; }\n    .row { display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; margin-top:8px; }\n    .info { font-size:13px; color:var(--muted); margin-top:8px; }\n    pre.codeview { background:transparent; padding:10px; border-radius:6px; font-family:monospace; font-size:13px; color:#e6eef8; overflow:auto; border:1px dashed rgba(255,255,255,0.03); min-height:140px; }\n    .code-span { background:transparent; }\n    .code-highlight { background:linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(34,197,94,0.14), rgba(56,189,248,0.06)); border-radius:3px; color:#dff8ff; }\n    .ast-tree { overflow:auto; padding:8px; border-radius:6px; border:1px dashed rgba(255,255,255,0.03); background:transparent; flex:1; }\n    ul.tree { list-style:none; padding-left:18px; margin:6px 0; color:var(--muted); }\n    ul.tree li { margin:4px 0; cursor:pointer; }\n    .node-label { padding:6px 8px; border-radius:6px; display:inline-block; background:var(--node); color:#cfeeff; font-weight:600; }\n    .node-meta { font-size:12px; color:var(--muted); margin-left:8px; font-weight:400; }\n    .node-selected { box-shadow:0 6px 20px rgba(124,58,237,0.12); background:linear-gradient(90deg,#222e4a,#12305a); color:#fff; }\n    .details { font-size:13px; color:var(--muted); margin-top:8px; padding:8px; border-radius:6px; border:1px dashed rgba(255,255,255,0.03); min-height:60px; }\n    .output { background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.1), rgba(255,255,255,0.02)); padding:10px; border-radius:6px; font-family:monospace; font-size:13px; min-height:80px; color:#dff8ff; border:1px dashed rgba(255,255,255,0.03); overflow:auto; }\n    input[type=\"text\"] { background:transparent; border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04); color:var(--muted); padding:6px 8px; border-radius:6px; }\n    label { font-size:13px; color:var(--muted); }\n    .small-muted { font-size:12px; color:#7b8798; }\n    .footer { margin-top:8px; font-size:12px; color:#7b8798; }\n    .toolbar { display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:8px; }\n    .controls-right { display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; margin-left:auto; }\n    .badge { background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03); padding:6px 8px; border-radius:6px; color:var(--muted); font-size:12px; }\n    .switch { display:inline-flex; gap:6px; align-items:center; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"wrap\">\n    <div class=\"col small\" style=\"flex:0 0 420px;\">\n      <h1>AST Playground — Source</h1>\n      <textarea id=\"code\" spellcheck=\"false\">// Try editing the code and click Parse\nlet x = 2 + 3 * 4;\nlet y = x + 1;\nprint(y);\nx = x + 10;\nprint(x);\n\nfunction style is limited — this demo implements a tiny language:\n- let declarations\n- assignments\n- arithmetic + - * / ^ (power)\n- function calls (e.g. print)\n- semicolons optional (parser will accept newlines)\n</textarea>\n\n      <div class=\"controls\">\n        <button id=\"parseBtn\" class=\"primary\">Parse ↔ Generate</button>\n        <button id=\"evalBtn\">Evaluate</button>\n        <button id=\"foldBtn\">Transform: Constant-fold</button>\n        <button id=\"renameBtn\">Transform: Rename</button>\n        <button id=\"resetBtn\" class=\"danger\">Reset Code</button>\n        <div style=\"flex:1\"></div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"row\">\n        <label>Rename: </label>\n        <input id=\"renameFrom\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"oldName\" style=\"width:110px;\"/>\n        <input id=\"renameTo\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"newName\" style=\"width:110px;\"/>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"info\">\n        - Click nodes in the AST to highlight the source fragment and show metadata. <br/>\n        - Use \"Constant-fold\" to simplify constant expressions in the AST. <br/>\n        - \"Parse ↔ Generate\" parses the source and regenerates formatted code from the AST below.\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"footer\">Language: tiny subset for demonstration (not full JavaScript)</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"col\">\n      <h1>AST Visualization</h1>\n\n      <div class=\"toolbar\">\n        <div class=\"badge\" id=\"status\">Status: idle</div>\n        <div class=\"controls-right\">\n          <button id=\"trPre\">Traverse: Pre-order</button>\n          <button id=\"trPost\">Traverse: Post-order</button>\n          <button id=\"stopTraverse\">Stop</button>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"ast-tree\" id=\"astTree\" aria-live=\"polite\">\n        <!-- AST will render here -->\n        <div class=\"small-muted\">No AST yet. Parse some code.</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"details\" id=\"nodeDetails\">\n        <div style=\"font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);\">Node Info</div>\n        <div id=\"nodeInfo\">Select a node to inspect.</div>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"col small\" style=\"flex:0 0 420px;\">\n      <h1>Code, Output & Actions</h1>\n\n      <div style=\"display:flex; gap:6px;\">\n        <div style=\"flex:1;\">\n          <div class=\"small-muted\">Generated code (from AST)</div>\n          <pre id=\"generated\" class=\"codeview\"></pre>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <div class=\"small-muted\">Console Output (print)</div>\n        <div id=\"output\" class=\"output\"></div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <div class=\"small-muted\">Raw AST (JSON)</div>\n        <pre id=\"astJson\" class=\"codeview\" style=\"height:160px; overflow:auto;\"></pre>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n<script>\n/*\n  Tiny language parser + AST demo\n  - Programs: sequences of statements\n  - Statements: let IDENT = expr; | IDENT = expr; | expr; | function calls as expr;\n  - Expressions: numbers, identifiers, parentheses, binary ops + - * / ^, function calls\n  - Tracks start/end indices for nodes\n  - Provides AST visualization, traversal, transformations, code generation, evaluation\n*/\n\n(function(){\n  // Utilities\n  function escapeHtml(s) {\n    return s.replace(/[&<>\"']/g, function(m){\n      return {'&':'&amp;','<':'&lt;','>':'&gt;','\"':'&quot;',\"'\":'&#39;'}[m];\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Tokenizer\n  function tokenize(input) {\n    const tokens = [];\n    const len = input.length;\n    let i = 0;\n    const isWhitespace = ch => /\\s/.test(ch);\n    const isDigit = ch => /[0-9]/.test(ch);\n    const isIdentStart = ch => /[a-zA-Z_]/.test(ch);\n    const isIdent = ch => /[a-zA-Z0-9_]/.test(ch);\n\n    while (i < len) {\n      const ch = input[i];\n      if (isWhitespace(ch)) { i++; continue; }\n      const start = i;\n      // numbers (integer/float)\n      if (isDigit(ch) || (ch === '.' && isDigit(input[i+1]))) {\n        let num = '';\n        while (i < len && /[0-9.]/.test(input[i])) { num += input[i++]; }\n        tokens.push({type:'number', value:num, start, end:i});\n        continue;\n      }\n      // identifiers / keywords\n      if (isIdentStart(ch)) {\n        let id = '';\n        while (i < len && isIdent(input[i])) id += input[i++];\n        const type = (id === 'let' || id === 'function') ? 'keyword' : 'identifier';\n        // treat 'print' as identifier (call)\n        tokens.push({type, value:id, start, end:i});\n        continue;\n      }\n      // two-character operators? None needed except maybe '==' not supported\n      // single char punctuators/operators\n      const single = {\n        '+':'operator','-':'operator','*':'operator','/':'operator','^':'operator',\n        '(':'punct',' )':'punct',')':'punct','=':'operator',';':'punct',',':'punct','{':'punct','}':'punct'\n      };\n      if (single[ch]) {\n        tokens.push({type:single[ch], value:ch, start, end:++i});\n        continue;\n      }\n      // unknown char: treat as single-character token\n      tokens.push({type:'unknown', value:ch, start, end:++i});\n    }\n    tokens.push({type:'eof', value:'', start:input.length, end:input.length});\n    return tokens;\n  }\n\n  // Parser (Pratt)\n  function parseProgram(input) {\n    const tokens = tokenize(input);\n    let pos = 0;\n    function peek(n=0){ return tokens[pos + n] || tokens[tokens.length-1]; }\n    function consume(expectType, expectValue) {\n      const t = peek();\n      if (expectType && t.type !== expectType) throw parseError(`Expected ${expectType} but got ${t.type}`, t);\n      if (expectValue && t.value !== expectValue) throw parseError(`Expected ${expectValue} but got ${t.value}`, t);\n      pos++;\n      return t;\n    }\n    function parseError(msg, token) {\n      const t = token || peek();\n      const e = new Error(msg + \" at pos \" + t.start + \"-\" + t.end + \" near '\" + input.slice(t.start, t.end) + \"'\");\n      e._token = t;\n      throw e;\n    }\n\n    function isPunct(val){ return peek().type === 'punct' && peek().value === val; }\n    function isOperator(op){ return peek().type === 'operator' && peek().value === op; }\n\n    // precedence table\n    const PRECEDENCE = {\n      '=':1,\n      '+':10,'-':10,\n      '*':20,'/':20,\n      '^':30\n    };\n\n    function parseProgramBody() {\n      const body = [];\n      while (peek().type !== 'eof') {\n        // allow automatic semicolon via newline? tokens don't contain newline; so require semicolon optional if next is keyword or eof\n        // we'll parse statement and swallow optional semicolon\n        const stmt = parseStatement();\n        if (stmt) body.push(stmt);\n      }\n      return { type:'Program', body, start: body.length?body[0].start:0, end: body.length?body[body.length-1].end:0 };\n    }\n\n    function parseStatement() {\n      const t = peek();\n      if (t.type === 'keyword' && t.value === 'let') {\n        const start = t.start;\n        consume('keyword','let');\n        const id = consume('identifier');\n        if (!id) parseError(\"Expected identifier after let\", peek());\n        // optional '='\n        if (isOperator('=')) {\n          consume('operator','=');\n          const init = parseExpression();\n          // semicolon optional\n          if (isPunct(';')) consume('punct',';');\n          const node = {\n            type:'VariableDeclaration',\n            id: { type:'Identifier', name:id.value, start:id.start, end:id.end },\n            init,\n            start, end: init.end\n          };\n          return node;\n        } else {\n          parseError(\"let must be followed by =\", peek());\n        }\n      }\n      // assignment: IDENT = expr ;\n      if (peek().type === 'identifier' && peek(1).type === 'operator' && peek(1).value === '=') {\n        const idTok = consume('identifier');\n        const start = idTok.start;\n        consume('operator','=');\n        const expr = parseExpression();\n        if (isPunct(';')) consume('punct',';');\n        return {\n          type:'AssignmentExpression',\n          operator:'=',\n          left: { type:'Identifier', name:idTok.value, start:idTok.start, end:idTok.end },\n          right: expr,\n          start, end: expr.end\n        };\n      }\n      // other expression statements (including function calls)\n      const expr = parseExpression();\n      if (isPunct(';')) consume('punct',';');\n      return {\n        type:'ExpressionStatement',\n        expression: expr,\n        start: expr.start,\n        end: expr.end\n      };\n    }\n\n    function parseExpression(rbp=0) {\n      let t = peek();\n      let left;\n      // nud\n      if (t.type === 'number') {\n        consume('number');\n        left = { type:'Literal', value: Number(t.value), raw: t.value, start: t.start, end: t.end };\n      } else if (t.type === 'identifier') {\n        consume('identifier');\n        left = { type:'Identifier', name: t.value, start: t.start, end: t.end };\n      } else if (t.type === 'punct' && t.value === '(') {\n        consume('punct','(');\n        const expr = parseExpression();\n        if (!(peek().type === 'punct' && peek().value === ')')) throw parseError(\"Expected )\", peek());\n        const r = consume('punct',')');\n        left = { type:'GroupExpression', expression: expr, start: t.start, end: r.end };\n      } else if (t.type === 'operator' && (t.value === '+' || t.value === '-')) {\n        // unary\n        consume('operator');\n        const right = parseExpression(PRECEDENCE[t.value] || 50);\n        left = { type:'UnaryExpression', operator: t.value, argument: right, start: t.start, end: right.end };\n      } else {\n        throw parseError(\"Unexpected token in expression\", t);\n      }\n\n      // led\n      while (true) {\n        const next = peek();\n        if (next.type === 'operator' && PRECEDENCE[next.value] !== undefined) {\n          const op = next.value;\n          const prec = PRECEDENCE[op];\n          const isRightAssoc = (op === '^');\n          if (prec < rbp) break;\n          consume('operator', op);\n          const right = parseExpression(isRightAssoc ? prec : prec + 1);\n          const newStart = left.start;\n          left = { type:'BinaryExpression', operator:op, left, right, start:newStart, end:right.end };\n          continue;\n        }\n        // function call: Identifier ( args )\n        if (peek().type === 'punct' && peek().value === '(') {\n          // call\n          const startCall = left.start;\n          consume('punct','(');\n          const args = [];\n          if (!(peek().type === 'punct' && peek().value === ')')) {\n            while (true) {\n              args.push(parseExpression());\n              if (peek().type === 'punct' && peek().value === ',') {\n                consume('punct',','); continue;\n              } else break;\n            }\n          }\n          const rp = consume('punct',')');\n          left = { type:'CallExpression', callee:left, arguments: args, start:startCall, end:rp.end };\n          continue;\n        }\n        break;\n      }\n      return left;\n    }\n\n    const ast = parseProgramBody();\n    return ast;\n  }\n\n  // Code generator (pretty-print)\n  function generate(node) {\n    switch(node.type) {\n      case 'Program': return node.body.map(generate).join(\"\\\\n\");\n      case 'VariableDeclaration':\n        return 'let ' + node.id.name + ' = ' + generate(node.init) + ';';\n      case 'AssignmentExpression':\n        return generate(node.left) + ' = ' + generate(node.right) + ';';\n      case 'ExpressionStatement':\n        return generate(node.expression) + ';';\n      case 'BinaryExpression': {\n        const op = node.operator;\n        const left = needsParens(node.left, node.operator) ? '('+generate(node.left)+')' : generate(node.left);\n        const right = needsParens(node.right, node.operator, false) ? '('+generate(node.right)+')' : generate(node.right);\n        return left + ' ' + op + ' ' + right;\n      }\n      case 'UnaryExpression':\n        return node.operator + generate(node.argument);\n      case 'Literal':\n        return String(node.raw != null ? node.raw : node.value);\n      case 'Identifier':\n        return node.name;\n      case 'CallExpression':\n        return generate(node.callee) + '(' + node.arguments.map(generate).join(', ') + ')';\n      case 'GroupExpression':\n        return '(' + generate(node.expression) + ')';\n      default:\n        return '[Unknown:' + node.type + ']';\n    }\n  }\n\n  // decision to parenthesize based on operator precedence\n  function precedenceOf(op) {\n    if (op === '^') return 30;\n    if (op === '*' || op === '/') return 20;\n    if (op === '+' || op === '-') return 10;\n    return 1;\n  }\n  function needsParens(child, parentOp, isLeft=true) {\n    if (!child) return false;\n    if (child.type !== 'BinaryExpression') return false;\n    const cp = precedenceOf(child.operator);\n    const pp = precedenceOf(parentOp);\n    if (cp < pp) return true;\n    if (cp === pp) {\n      // for right-associative '^', parent op equal needs parens on left?\n      if (parentOp === '^') {\n        return !isLeft; // exponent is right-assoc: a ^ (b ^ c) okay; (a ^ b) ^ c needs parens on right? Keep simple: when equal and it's right-assoc, parens on left\n      }\n      // for left-assoc, parens on right if equal\n      return !isLeft;\n    }\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  // Simple evaluator for this tiny language\n  function evaluateProgram(ast, options={print:console.log}) {\n    const env = Object.create(null);\n    const output = [];\n    function evalNode(node) {\n      switch(node.type) {\n        case 'Program':\n          for (const s of node.body) evalNode(s);\n          return;\n        case 'VariableDeclaration': {\n          const name = node.id.name;\n          const val = evalNode(node.init);\n          env[name] = val;\n          return val;\n        }\n        case 'AssignmentExpression': {\n          const name = node.left.name;\n          const val = evalNode(node.right);\n          env[name] = val;\n          return val;\n        }\n        case 'ExpressionStatement': return evalNode(node.expression);\n        case 'BinaryExpression': {\n          const a = evalNode(node.left);\n          const b = evalNode(node.right);\n          switch(node.operator) {\n            case '+': return a + b;\n            case '-': return a - b;\n            case '*': return a * b;\n            case '/': return a / b;\n            case '^': return Math.pow(a,b);\n          }\n        }\n        case 'UnaryExpression': {\n          const v = evalNode(node.argument);\n          return node.operator === '-' ? -v : +v;\n        }\n        case 'Literal': return node.value;\n        case 'Identifier': {\n          if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(env, node.name)) return env[node.name];\n          // undefined variables default to 0 for demo\n          return undefined;\n        }\n        case 'CallExpression': {\n          const callee = node.callee;\n          const args = node.arguments.map(evalNode);\n          if (callee.type === 'Identifier' && callee.name === 'print') {\n            const out = args.map(a => typeof a === 'undefined' ? 'undefined' : String(a)).join(' ');\n            output.push(out);\n            if (options.print) options.print(out);\n            return out;\n          } else {\n            // no user functions in this tiny demo\n            return undefined;\n          }\n        }\n        case 'GroupExpression': return evalNode(node.expression);\n      }\n    }\n    evalNode(ast);\n    return output;\n  }\n\n  // AST traversal utilities\n  function walk(node, fn, parent=null, prop=null, index=null) {\n    if (!node) return;\n    fn(node, parent, prop, index);\n    // children according to types\n    switch(node.type) {\n      case 'Program':\n        node.body.forEach((c,i)=>walk(c,fn,node,'body',i)); break;\n      case 'VariableDeclaration':\n        walk(node.id,fn,node,'id',null);\n        walk(node.init,fn,node,'init',null); break;\n      case 'AssignmentExpression':\n        walk(node.left,fn,node,'left',null);\n        walk(node.right,fn,node,'right',null); break;\n      case 'ExpressionStatement':\n        walk(node.expression,fn,node,'expression',null); break;\n      case 'BinaryExpression':\n        walk(node.left,fn,node,'left',null);\n        walk(node.right,fn,node,'right',null); break;\n      case 'UnaryExpression':\n        walk(node.argument,fn,node,'argument',null); break;\n      case 'CallExpression':\n        walk(node.callee,fn,node,'callee',null);\n        node.arguments.forEach((c,i)=>walk(c,fn,node,'arguments',i)); break;\n      case 'GroupExpression':\n        walk(node.expression,fn,node,'expression',null); break;\n      default:\n        // Identifier, Literal: no children\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Transformation: constant folding\n  function constantFold(ast) {\n    walk(ast, function(node,parent,prop,index){\n      if (node.type === 'BinaryExpression') {\n        const L = node.left, R = node.right;\n        if (L.type === 'Literal' && R.type === 'Literal') {\n          const a = L.value, b = R.value;\n          let res;\n          switch(node.operator) {\n            case '+': res = a + b; break;\n            case '-': res = a - b; break;\n            case '*': res = a * b; break;\n            case '/': res = a / b; break;\n            case '^': res = Math.pow(a,b); break;\n            default: res = null;\n          }\n          if (res !== null) {\n            const lit = { type:'Literal', value:res, raw:String(res), start:node.start, end:node.end };\n            // replace in parent\n            if (parent) {\n              if (prop === 'left') parent.left = lit;\n              else if (prop === 'right') parent.right = lit;\n              else if (prop === 'init') parent.init = lit;\n              else if (prop === 'expression') parent.expression = lit;\n              else if (Array.isArray(parent[prop])) parent[prop][index] = lit;\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      // unary folding\n      if (node.type === 'UnaryExpression' && node.argument.type === 'Literal') {\n        const v = node.argument.value;\n        const res = node.operator === '-' ? -v : +v;\n        const lit = { type:'Literal', value:res, raw:String(res), start:node.start, end:node.end };\n        if (parent) {\n          if (prop === 'left') parent.left = lit;\n          else if (prop === 'right') parent.right = lit;\n          else if (prop === 'init') parent.init = lit;\n          else if (prop === 'expression') parent.expression = lit;\n          else if (Array.isArray(parent[prop])) parent[prop][index] = lit;\n        }\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Transformation: rename identifiers\n  function renameIdentifier(ast, from, to) {\n    walk(ast, function(node,parent,prop,index){\n      if (node.type === 'Identifier' && node.name === from) {\n        node.name = to;\n      }\n      // For declaration id itself handled via Identifier node replacement\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Render AST as nested list\n  function renderAST(ast, container, onSelect) {\n    container.innerHTML = '';\n    if (!ast) {\n      container.innerHTML = '<div class=\"small-muted\">No AST.</div>';\n      return;\n    }\n    function createNodeElement(node) {\n      const li = document.createElement('li');\n      li.className = 'ast-node';\n      const label = document.createElement('span');\n      label.className = 'node-label';\n      label.textContent = node.type;\n      li.appendChild(label);\n      const meta = document.createElement('span');\n      meta.className = 'node-meta';\n      meta.textContent = metaText(node);\n      li.appendChild(meta);\n      li.dataset.start = node.start || 0;\n      li.dataset.end = node.end || 0;\n\n      label.onclick = (e) => {\n        e.stopPropagation();\n        selectNode(node);\n      };\n      meta.onclick = (e) => { e.stopPropagation(); selectNode(node); };\n\n      // children\n      const children = childrenOf(node);\n      if (children && children.length) {\n        const ul = document.createElement('ul');\n        ul.className = 'tree';\n        children.forEach(ch => {\n          const cLi = createNodeElement(ch);\n          ul.appendChild(cLi);\n        });\n        li.appendChild(ul);\n      }\n      return li;\n    }\n\n    function childrenOf(node) {\n      switch(node.type) {\n        case 'Program': return node.body;\n        case 'VariableDeclaration': return [node.id, node.init];\n        case 'AssignmentExpression': return [node.left, node.right];\n        case 'ExpressionStatement': return [node.expression];\n        case 'BinaryExpression': return [node.left, node.right];\n        case 'UnaryExpression': return [node.argument];\n        case 'CallExpression': return [node.callee].concat(node.arguments);\n        case 'GroupExpression': return [node.expression];\n        default: return [];\n      }\n    }\n\n    function metaText(node) {\n      switch(node.type) {\n        case 'Identifier': return node.name;\n        case 'Literal': return String(node.raw != null ? node.raw : node.value);\n        case 'VariableDeclaration': return node.id ? node.id.name : '';\n        case 'AssignmentExpression': return node.left && node.left.name ? node.left.name : '';\n        case 'BinaryExpression': return node.operator;\n        case 'UnaryExpression': return node.operator;\n        case 'CallExpression': return 'call';\n        default: return '';\n      }\n    }\n\n    function selectNode(node) {\n      // clear previous selection classes\n      container.querySelectorAll('.node-selected').forEach(el => el.classList.remove('node-selected'));\n      // find the corresponding label in DOM by matching node positions\n      const match = findElemByPos(container, node.start, node.end);\n      if (match) {\n        match.classList.add('node-selected');\n      }\n      if (onSelect) onSelect(node);\n    }\n\n    function findElemByPos(el, start, end) {\n      const nodes = el.querySelectorAll('[data-start]');\n      for (const n of nodes) {\n        if (Number(n.dataset.start) === (start||0) && Number(n.dataset.end) === (end||0)) return n.querySelector('.node-label') || n;\n      }\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    const rootUL = document.createElement('ul');\n    rootUL.className = 'tree';\n    const rootLi = createNodeElement(ast);\n    rootUL.appendChild(rootLi);\n    container.appendChild(rootUL);\n  }\n\n  // Show node detail\n  function showNodeInfo(node, codeEl, detailEl) {\n    const info = [];\n    info.push('<div><b>Type:</b> ' + node.type + '</div>');\n    if (node.type === 'Identifier') info.push('<div><b>Name:</b> ' + node.name + '</div>');\n    if (node.type === 'Literal') info.push('<div><b>Value:</b> ' + node.value + '</div>');\n    if (node.type === 'BinaryExpression') info.push('<div><b>Operator:</b> ' + node.operator + '</div>');\n    if (node.start != null) info.push('<div><b>Range:</b> ' + node.start + ' — ' + node.end + '</div>');\n    detailEl.innerHTML = info.join('');\n    // highlight in code view\n    highlightRangeInCode(codeEl, node.start, node.end);\n  }\n\n  // Highlight range in the code preview (generated area)\n  function highlightRangeInCode(codeEl, s, e) {\n    const codeInput = document.getElementById('code');\n    const src = codeInput.value;\n    const start = Math.max(0, s||0);\n    const end = Math.min(src.length, e||0);\n    const before = escapeHtml(src.slice(0,start));\n    const mid = escapeHtml(src.slice(start,end));\n    const after = escapeHtml(src.slice(end));\n    codeEl.innerHTML = before + '<span class=\"code-highlight code-span\">' + mid + '</span>' + after;\n  }\n\n  // Render JSON of AST\n  function astToJson(ast) {\n    return JSON.stringify(ast, function replacer(key,val){\n      // avoid circular or huge data; keep positions & values\n      if (key === 'start' || key === 'end' || key === 'type' || key === 'name' || key === 'value' || key === 'raw' || key === 'operator') {\n        return val;\n      }\n      // keep structural fields\n      if (typeof val === 'object' && val !== null) {\n        const t = val.type;\n        if (t) {\n          // limit depth by pruning functions\n          const clone = {};\n          for (const k in val) {\n            if (['type','name','value','raw','start','end','operator'].includes(k)) clone[k] = val[k];\n            if (k === 'arguments' || k === 'body' || k === 'left' || k === 'right' || k==='init' || k==='expression' || k==='callee' || k==='id') {\n              clone[k] = val[k];\n            }\n          }\n          return clone;\n        }\n      }\n      return val;\n    }, 2);\n  }\n\n  // Traversal animation\n  let traversalTimer = null;\n  function traverseAnimate(ast, order='pre', speed=600, onStep) {\n    const nodes = [];\n    if (order === 'pre') {\n      walk(ast, (n)=>nodes.push(n));\n    } else {\n      // post-order: collect leaves first\n      const post = [];\n      function postWalk(node) {\n        switch(node.type) {\n          case 'Program': node.body.forEach(postWalk); break;\n          case 'VariableDeclaration': postWalk(node.id); postWalk(node.init); break;\n          case 'AssignmentExpression': postWalk(node.left); postWalk(node.right); break;\n          case 'ExpressionStatement': postWalk(node.expression); break;\n          case 'BinaryExpression': postWalk(node.left); postWalk(node.right); break;\n          case 'UnaryExpression': postWalk(node.argument); break;\n          case 'CallExpression': postWalk(node.callee); node.arguments.forEach(postWalk); break;\n          case 'GroupExpression': postWalk(node.expression); break;\n          default: break;\n        }\n        post.push(node);\n      }\n      postWalk(ast);\n      nodes.push(...post);\n    }\n    let i = 0;\n    traversalTimer = setInterval(() => {\n      if (i >= nodes.length) { clearInterval(traversalTimer); traversalTimer = null; return; }\n      onStep(nodes[i++]);\n    }, speed);\n  }\n  function stopTraversal() { if (traversalTimer) { clearInterval(traversalTimer); traversalTimer = null; } }\n\n  // DOM references\n  const codeInput = document.getElementById('code');\n  const parseBtn = document.getElementById('parseBtn');\n  const evalBtn = document.getElementById('evalBtn');\n  const foldBtn = document.getElementById('foldBtn');\n  const renameBtn = document.getElementById('renameBtn');\n  const resetBtn = document.getElementById('resetBtn');\n  const astTree = document.getElementById('astTree');\n  const generatedEl = document.getElementById('generated');\n  const outputEl = document.getElementById('output');\n  const astJsonEl = document.getElementById('astJson');\n  const nodeDetails = document.getElementById('nodeInfo');\n  const statusEl = document.getElementById('status');\n  const trPre = document.getElementById('trPre');\n  const trPost = document.getElementById('trPost');\n  const stopTraverseBtn = document.getElementById('stopTraverse');\n  const renameFrom = document.getElementById('renameFrom');\n  const renameTo = document.getElementById('renameTo');\n\n  let currentAST = null;\n  let lastSource = codeInput.value;\n\n  function setStatus(s) { statusEl.textContent = 'Status: ' + s; }\n\n  function parseAndRender() {\n    const src = codeInput.value;\n    try {\n      const ast = parseProgram(src);\n      currentAST = ast;\n      setStatus('Parsed successfully');\n      // Render AST\n      renderAST(ast, astTree, (node) => {\n        showNodeInfo(node, generatedEl, nodeDetails);\n      });\n      // show generated code\n      generatedEl.textContent = generate(ast);\n      // show raw AST JSON\n      astJsonEl.textContent = JSON.stringify(currentAST, null, 2);\n      // highlight nothing initially\n      highlightRangeInCode(generatedEl, 0, 0);\n      nodeDetails.innerHTML = '<div class=\"small-muted\">Click a node to inspect details.</div>';\n    } catch (err) {\n      setStatus('Parse error');\n      astTree.innerHTML = '<div style=\"color:var(--danger);font-weight:700;\">Parse error: ' + escapeHtml(err.message) + '</div>';\n      generatedEl.textContent = '';\n      astJsonEl.textContent = '';\n      nodeDetails.innerHTML = '<div style=\"color:var(--danger);\">Fix errors in source and try again.</div>';\n    }\n  }\n\n  parseBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    parseAndRender();\n  });\n\n  evalBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    if (!currentAST) parseAndRender();\n    outputEl.textContent = '';\n    try {\n      const out = evaluateProgram(currentAST, { print: (s) => { outputEl.textContent += s + '\\\\n'; } });\n      setStatus('Evaluated');\n    } catch(err) {\n      outputEl.textContent = 'Runtime error: ' + err.message;\n      setStatus('Runtime error');\n    }\n  });\n\n  foldBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    if (!currentAST) parseAndRender();\n    constantFold(currentAST);\n    parseAndRender(); // re-render (parsing not necessary but regenerate visuals)\n    setStatus('Constant-fold applied');\n  });\n\n  renameBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    const from = renameFrom.value.trim();\n    const to = renameTo.value.trim();\n    if (!from || !to) { alert('Provide both from and to names'); return; }\n    if (!currentAST) parseAndRender();\n    renameIdentifier(currentAST, from, to);\n    // regenerate code and ast\n    generatedEl.textContent = generate(currentAST);\n    astJsonEl.textContent = JSON.stringify(currentAST, null, 2);\n    renderAST(currentAST, astTree, (node)=> showNodeInfo(node, generatedEl, nodeDetails));\n    setStatus('Renamed ' + from + ' → ' + to);\n  });\n\n  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    if (!confirm('Reset source to the original example?')) return;\n    codeInput.value = `// Try editing the code and click Parse\nlet x = 2 + 3 * 4;\nlet y = x + 1;\nprint(y);\nx = x + 10;\nprint(x);\n\nfunction style is limited — this demo implements a tiny language:\n- let declarations\n- assignments\n- arithmetic + - * / ^\n- function calls (e.g. print)\n- semicolons optional (parser will accept newlines)\n`;\n    parseAndRender();\n    outputEl.textContent = '';\n    setStatus('Reset code');\n  });\n\n  // Traversal controls\n  trPre.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    if (!currentAST) parseAndRender();\n    stopTraversal();\n    setStatus('Traversing (pre-order)...');\n    traverseAnimate(currentAST, 'pre', 600, (node)=> {\n      renderAST(currentAST, astTree, (n)=> showNodeInfo(n, generatedEl, nodeDetails));\n      // highlight the node\n      renderAST(currentAST, astTree, (n)=> showNodeInfo(n, generatedEl, nodeDetails));\n      // find node in DOM and add highlight\n      const match = astTree.querySelector('[data-start=\"'+(node.start||0)+'\"][data-end=\"'+(node.end||0)+'\"]');\n      astTree.querySelectorAll('.node-selected').forEach(el=>el.classList.remove('node-selected'));\n      if (match) {\n        const label = match.querySelector('.node-label');\n        if (label) label.classList.add('node-selected');\n      }\n      showNodeInfo(node, generatedEl, nodeDetails);\n    });\n  });\n  trPost.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    if (!currentAST) parseAndRender();\n    stopTraversal();\n    setStatus('Traversing (post-order)...');\n    traverseAnimate(currentAST, 'post', 600, (node)=> {\n      renderAST(currentAST, astTree, (n)=> showNodeInfo(n, generatedEl, nodeDetails));\n      const match = astTree.querySelector('[data-start=\"'+(node.start||0)+'\"][data-end=\"'+(node.end||0)+'\"]');\n      astTree.querySelectorAll('.node-selected').forEach(el=>el.classList.remove('node-selected'));\n      if (match) {\n        const label = match.querySelector('.node-label');\n        if (label) label.classList.add('node-selected');\n      }\n      showNodeInfo(node, generatedEl, nodeDetails);\n    });\n  });\n  stopTraverseBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){ stopTraversal(); setStatus('idle'); });\n\n  // initial parse\n  parseAndRender();\n\n  // When user clicks a node in AST, the renderAST's onSelect will call showNodeInfo and highlight code.\n  // But to better reflect selected highlight in the generated code area (left side), we map to original source by indices.\n  // generatedEl is used to show highlighted source (it contains the original code with highlighted spans)\n  // That's handled in showNodeInfo -> highlightRangeInCode\n\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
